        // If $a_{n-1}$ is in Class 1, then there are at most $k_1$ elements in Class 1 that are strictly greater than $a_{n-1}$.
        // And there are at most $k_1$ elements in Class 1 that are strictly smaller than $a_{n-1}$.
        //
        // Let's use a simpler argument.
        // Sort all $2n$ students: $a_0 \le a_1 \le \dots \le a_{2n-1}$.
